                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 3892/2.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Snyder</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jamaica</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-01-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 16, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Fearful earthquake followed by fire; Kingston destroyed; hundreds of lives lost;
                    food sadly wanted. Consulate partially destroyed; fireproof safe.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consul.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
